      "content": "it's hard to call it a \"balance\" when one side gets massive new subsidies and the other side just gets told they're part of a necessary cost. if we assume the green transition is inevitable, isn't the bill basically just picking winners and losers rather than being a neutral policy? it feels like it's deciding that coal communities are just meant to be left behind.",
